FBIS4-23835 "drafr116_e_94008" FBIS-AFR-94-116 Daily Report 15 Jun 1994 WEST AFRICA Nigeria Jailed Opposition Leader Begins Hunger Strike Jailed Opposition Leader Begins Hunger Strike AB1506195394 London BBC World Service in English 1705 GMT 15 Jun 94 AB1506195394 London BBC World Service English BFN [From the "African News"] [Text] Imprisoned chairman of Nigeria's Campaign for Democracy, Dr. Beko Ransome-Kuti, says he has begun a hunger strike. In a letter from Alagbon Police Station in Lagos to the attorney general and justice minister, Olu Onagoruwa, Dr. Ransome-Kuti said he had been kept in appalling circumstances without food. He said that after reporting to the police last week, he should have been kept in court or granted bail. Dr. Ransome-Kuti was jailed after the Campaign for Democracy called for street protests against the military government, to mark the anniversary of last year's annulled presidential elections on 12 June.
